pr.body:
Hard-refreshing `/feed` could render the mobile UI smaller than the client-navigation layout. The feed shell should keep the same sizing across direct loads and in-app navigation without changing feed design or behavior.

- **Feed shell sizing**
  - Remove the global `.main-content` max-width, padding, margin, and page animation only when rendering `.feed-page`.
  - Keeps `/feed` full-width on direct refresh while leaving other routes unchanged.

```css
main.main-content:has(.feed-page) {
  max-width: none;
  width: 100%;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  animation: none;
}
```

- **Service worker cache**
  - Bump the service worker cache version so stale cached feed shell assets are evicted after deploy.
